-- China's 2010 Foreign Trade About $2.8 Trillion, Commerce Ministry Says
-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 2010-11-01T03:34:47Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-01/china-s-2010-foreign-trade-about-2-8-trillion-commerce-ministry-says.html
China’s 2010 exports and imports will
rise 25 percent from a year earlier to about $2.8 trillion, the
Ministry of Commerce said in a statement on its website today.  China’s outbound investment growth may slow in 2011, the
ministry said in the statement.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
